30","control":["Alt. Truck Route to US 30","Kearney","Downtown","Hastings"],"lat":null,"lng":null,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":24,"place":"Platte River","state":"NE","kind":"crossing","mileFromStart":365.5,"toNextMi":1.8,"note":"Junction toward Bridge","control":["Bridge"],"lat":41.05388889,"lng":-95.88138889,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":25,"place":"Precinct 5","state":"NE","kind":"town","mileFromStart":367.3,"toNextMi":null,"note":"Junction toward Aurora","control":["Aurora"],"lat":null,"lng":null,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":26,"place":"Centerville Precinct","state":"NE","kind":"park-entrance","mileFromStart":null,"toNextMi":null,"note":"Junction toward Beatrice","control":["Beatrice"],"lat":null,"lng":null,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":27,"place":"Saltillo Precinct","state":"NE","kind":"town","mileFromStart":null,"toNextMi":null,"note":"Junction toward Jamaica Avenue & Bennet Road","control":["Jamaica Avenue","Bennet Road","68th Street","70th Street","82nd Street","84th Street"],"lat":null,"lng":null,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":28,"place":"Stockton Precinct","state":"NE","kind":"town","mileFromStart":466.4,"toNextMi":5.3,"note":"Junction toward Bennet","control":["Bennet"],"lat":null,"lng":null,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":29,"place":"North Palmyra Precinct","state":"NE","kind":"town","mileFromStart":471.7,"toNextMi":1,"note":"Junction toward Eagle","control":["Eagle"],"lat":null,"lng":null,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":30,"place":"Palmyra","state":"NE","kind":"town","mileFromStart":472.7,"toNextMi":12,"note":"Junction toward Douglas","control":["Douglas"],"lat":null,"lng":null,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":31,"place":"Syracuse Precinct","state":"NE","kind":"town","mileFromStart":484.7,"toNextMi":7.9,"note":"Junction toward Syracuse","control":["Syracuse"],"lat":null,"lng":null,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":32,"place":"Delaware Precinct","state":"NE","kind":"town","mileFromStart":492.6,"toNextMi":9.3,"note":"Junction toward N-67 (46th Road)","control":["N-67 (46th Road)"],"lat":null,"lng":null,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":33,"place":"Nebraska City","state":"NE","kind":"town","mileFromStart":501.9,"toNextMi":1.8,"note":"Junction toward Nebraska City & Auburn","control":["Nebraska City","Auburn"],"lat":40.67583333,"lng":-95.86166667,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":34,"place":"Four Mile Precinct","state":"NE","kind":"town","mileFromStart":503.7,"toNextMi":0.3,"note":"Junction toward N-2 Bus. west (4th Corso)","control":["N-2 Bus. west (4th Corso)"],"lat":null,"lng":null,"src":"wikipedia"},{"seq":35,"place":"Missouri River","state":"NE","kind":"terminus","mileFromStart":504,"toNextMi":null,"note":"The drive ends here","control":["Nebraska City Bridge; Nebraska–Iowa line","Iowa"],"lat":null,"lng":null,"src":"wikipedia"}],"history":{"paragraphs":["The western segment of N-2 begins at the South Dakota border north of Crawford in a concurrency with N-71. The road goes east, southeast, and then south into Crawford. In Crawford, there is a concurrency with US 20. N-2 and N-71 both continue south from Crawford through Marsland, Nebraska. The two highways split west of Hemingford, Nebraska and N-2 turns east towards Hemingford. At Hemingford, N-2 turns southeast towards Alliance. At Berea, N-2 meets US 385 and the two overlap into Alliance.","At Alliance, N-2 goes east into the Sand Hills. It goes through several small towns, including Hyannis, Mullen and Thedford. In Thedford, N-2 briefly overlaps US 83. East of Thedford, near Halsey, is the Nebraska National Forest. At Dunning, N-2 intersects N-91 and turns southeasterly towards Broken Bow and Grand Island.","After turning southeasterly at Dunning, N-2 meets N-92 in Merna. The two highways overlap through Broken Bow and separate when they meet US 183 in Ansley. N-2 meets N-10 in Hazard, N-68 in Ravenna and N-11 in Cairo. On the northwest edge of Grand Island, N-2 becomes a four-lane divided highway and then encounters US 281. N-2 then follows US 281 along the western edge of Grand Island until it meets US 34 and then those two routes overlap through the southern edge of Grand Island. N-2 and US 34 cross the Platte River and shortly thereafter, they separate and N-2 turns south towards Interstate 80 (I-80). At I-80, the western segment of N-2 ends.","The eastern segment of N-2 begins as the Lincoln South Beltway, a freeway south of Lincoln, at a semi-directional T interchange with US 77. Passing by Lincoln to the south, N-2 becomes a four-lane divided highway following a diamond interchange with Nebraska Parkway, its former alignment through the city, southeast of it. It soon encounters several small towns and highways. It meets N-43 north of Bennet and overlaps it for 5 miles (8.0 km), until shortly before Palmyra. Near Syracuse, there is a bypass of that community and there is a freeway exit for N-50. It continues east and near Nebraska City, it meets US 75 and the two highways are together briefly until the southern edge of Nebraska City. Also at this intersection, N-2 Business begins and goes through Nebraska City. After they separate, N-2 heads east and then northeast, meets the eastern end of N-2 Business and crosses the Missouri River over the Nebraska City Bridge and enters Iowa. In Iowa, the highway continues as Iowa Highway 2."],"sourceSection":"Route description","src":"wikipedia"},"highlights":[{"n":"Platte River","d":"Junction toward Bridge","q":"Platte River","lat":41.05388889,"lng":-95.88138889,"src":"wikipedia"}],"references":[{"n":1,"text":"\"Nebraska Highway Reference Log Book\" (PDF). Nebraska Department of Roads. 2015. pp. 2–10. Archived from the original (PDF) on February 15, 2020. Retrieved January 6, 2017.","url":"https://web.archive.org/web/20200215123307/https://dot.nebraska.gov/media/6920/logbook.pdf"},{"n":2,"text":"\"overview of Nebraska Highway 2 western segment\" (Map). Google Maps. Retrieved November 10, 2010.","url":"https://maps.google.com/maps?f=d&source=s_d&saddr=nebraska+2+and+south+dakota+71&daddr=41.98183,-100.53034+to:nebraska+2+and+south+b+road&geocode=FU0mkAIdtl7S-SkDMxd4ZlZjhzFKVnNxaieTbA%3BFYaXgAIdXAcC-in3StPHrFadhzHPvkzAyplJCg%3BFVLabgIdH5wk-ilFfgqk1JGZhzEh7oZrE_Smvg&hl=en&mra=ls&sll=40.818421,-98.259659&sspn=0.02962,0.084543&ie=UTF8&t=h&z=7&via=1"},{"n":3,"text":"\"overview of Nebraska Highway 2 eastern segment\" (Map). Google Maps. Retrieved November 10, 2010.","url":"https://maps.google.com/maps?f=d&source=s_d&saddr=40.78726,+-96.731&daddr=Nebraska+2+%26+Iowa+2,+Percival,+Fremont,+Iowa+51648&geocode=FTxdbgIdiAA8-g%3BFTeebAId4cRJ-imBQlO1PVqUhzGenuyN6uC4Jw&hl=en&mra=ls&sll=40.720135,-96.27789&sspn=0.474615,1.352692&ie=UTF8&ll=40.720201,-96.28006&spn=0.474615,1.352692&t=h&z=10"},{"n":4,"text":"\"Lincoln South Beltway — Nebraska Department of Transportation\".","url":"https://dot.nebraska.gov/lincoln-south-beltway/"},{"n":5,"text":"Lampman, Ben (November 8, 2023). \"Nebraska DOT announces new segments open on Lincoln South Beltway\". KLKN-TV. Retrieved January 3, 2025.","url":"https://www.klkntv.com/nebraska-dot-announces-new-segments-open-on-lincoln-south-beltway/"},{"n":6,"text":"\"Overview map of N-2 Business\" (Map). Google Maps. Retrieved April 1, 2024.","url":"https://www.google.com/maps/dir/40.6715201,-95.9096027/40.6693969,-95.8965708/40.6729518,-95.8590082/40.6671411,-95.833825/@40.6577598,-95.9129183,13z/am=t/data=!3m1!4b1!4m7!4m6!1m0!1m0!1m0!1m1!4e1!3e0?entry=ttu"}]}